	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=65101><span id=Scholar>Drienne, Guardian of the Glade</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>293 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.41]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Pet focus effects had three main effects that you would immediately notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;First is the size.  Focused pets are considerably larger than non-focused pets.  Second is speed.  Focused pets run at SoW speed (though I'm not sure if Mage pets get natural speed boosts other than the Mage pet SoW spell).  Thirdly is damage.  Focused pets have a higher max hit (all hits, including backstab, I believe).</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76285 target=akztarg>Drienne Gardairne</a> -- 66 Ranger<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316502 target=akztarg>Xide Kyck</a> -- 65 Necromancer<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725442 target=akztarg>Hwel Jung</a> -- 65 Rogue</td></tr>
